HEADWORD: Highborn
<hw>High"born`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of noble or
aristocratic birth. Contrasted with <ant>lowborn</ant> and
<ant>common</ant>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> aristocratic, blue-blooded, coroneted, gentle,
patrician, titled, wellborn, upper-class.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

